- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/CoreIpcBus.cs
    Pure C# implementation of ICoreIpcBus. Constructor dependencies:
        - CoreIpcOptions (max message size + default request timeout)
        - IMessageCodec (envelope encode)
        - IIpcOutboundChannel (transport send)
        - RequestCorrelationRegistry (request correlation + timeout)
        - TopicSubscriptionRegistry (topic × kind handler delegation)
        - IConnectionDiagnostics (Diagnostics passthrough)
        - optional Func<long> timestampProvider (deterministic tests)
        - optional JsonSerializerOptions for payload (camelCase default)
        - optional logError callback
    Public API behavior:
        - PublishState/PublishEvent: validate non-empty topic →
          NotConnected check → BuildAndEncode → size limit check
          on encoded bytes (Req 3.9) → fire-and-forget SendAsync.
          Returns IpcResult.Fail(InvalidTopic|NotConnected|
          SizeLimitExceeded|TransportFailure) on any precheck miss
          or sync send failure; never throws (Req 5.4).
        - RequestAsync<TRequest,TResponse>: same prechecks + correlation
          id allocation (GUID-N) + RegisterPending(timeout, ct) +
          SendAsync. Awaits the pending JsonElement result and
          deserializes into TResponse. Honors RequestOptions.Timeout
          override (D-8) and falls back to CoreIpcOptions
          .DefaultRequestTimeout (= 5s). Send failures call
          FailPending(TransportFailure) so the awaiter resolves
          immediately and pending count stays at 0.
        - SubscribeState/SubscribeEvent<TPayload>: register a
          DispatchHandler under (topic, MessageKind.State|Event) that
          deserializes the JsonElement payload via the bus's payload
          serializer and invokes the typed callback. Returns the
          ISubscriptionToken from the registry directly.
        - RegisterRequestHandler<TRequest,TResponse>: register under
          (topic, MessageKind.Request) a DispatchHandler that fires
          the user's async handler, then encodes a Response envelope
          carrying the same correlationId and SendAsyncs it. Errors
          are isolated and logged via the optional logError hook.
        - Diagnostics returns the injected IConnectionDiagnostics.
    Internals:
        - BuildAndEncode is shared between Publish/Request/Response
          paths so the size check is uniform across all kinds.
        - Payload serializer defaults to camelCase + case-insensitive
          property matching so SystemTextJsonCodec round-trips with
          PoCo records. JsonElement payloads are passed through
          without re-serialization.
        - Synchronous SendAsync paths surface failures as
          TransportFailure; async sends are observed via a
          ContinueWith → logError to avoid swallowing background
          exceptions.
