Implementation summary:
- CoreIpcBus is the single entry point (Req 1.1, design.md §446) and
  is implemented in pure C# inside the existing
  VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef, with no Unity engine
  references — verified by the test harness which constructs and
  exercises the bus directly from EditMode without touching any
  PlayerLoop or MonoBehaviour.
- IIpcOutboundChannel is the new abstraction that decouples the bus
  from the concrete ITransportAdapter / IClientConnection topology.
  This keeps the bus testable today and lets the runtime composition
  task (7.1) decide whether to multiplex sends across multiple
  IClientConnections without changing the bus contract.
- The send precheck order is: empty/null topic → NotConnected →
  payload serialization → codec encode → size limit check on the
  ENCODED bytes → SendAsync. The size check operates on the encoded
  byte length so it matches what the receiving codec sees on the
  wire (Req 3.9 / 3.10 symmetry).
- RegisterRequestHandler delegates to TopicSubscriptionRegistry
  under MessageKind.Request as the registration key. The runtime
  composition (task 7.1) is responsible for routing inbound Request
  envelopes to that registry — MainThreadDispatchQueue intentionally
  rejects Request/Response envelopes today (it routes only State
  and Event), and the request handler test simulates that routing
  by invoking the registered DispatchHandler directly.
- Tests use a regular SamplePayload class (not a record) because
  Abstractions' IsExternalInit polyfill is internal and not visible
  to the test assembly, and adding another polyfill copy in the
  test asmdef would just duplicate code.

